      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed comprehensively across all model inputs including fluid viscosity, pump rotational speed, and hemolysis power-law exponents. Input distributions were assigned and 10,000-sample MC propagation completed. Reported 5th–95th percentile bounds on NIH. Achieved level reflects that input characterization is based on literature distributions rather than device-specific measurements, limiting confidence to gradation 2."
